      <tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>678 threads, <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=0>1</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=25>2</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=50>3</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=75>4</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=100>5</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=125>6</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=150>7</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=175>8</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=200>9</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=225>10</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=250>11</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=275>12</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=300>13</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=325>14</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=350>15</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=375>16</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=400>17</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=425>18</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=450>19</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=475>20</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=500>21</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=525>22</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=550>23</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=575>24</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=600>25</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=625>26</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=650>27</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=675>28</a>  page(s) long</td><td  style='font-size: 9.5px;' align=right>&nbsp;<a href=classes.html?class=7&start=25>Next Page</a></td></tr></table></form><a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7>Root thread</a><table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98336955474132></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98336955474132><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>keeping casters alive</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Feb 28th 9:12 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>i agree to a large part that the cleric needs to lay down the law in a group and force chain pulling of single mobs at a time, at a pretty fast pace.&nbsp;&nbsp;best use of mana and all.  so do this when you group.<br><br>for those situations you don't plan on, though--adds, extra agros from no where, spawns on the casters in the back, spawns during pulls--keep the casters alive.  best way to do this isn't healing them, it is stunning and rooting the mobs.  stun casts super fast, and usually agros the mob on you--this is scary but good, you have good ac and more hitpoints--then you root the mob, believe me, the casters will kill that mob so fast your head will spin.<br><br>casters understand what you just did for them right away.  and then they realize how bad the cleric roots are, the mob gets snared Dot'd nuked and fried so quick it is amazing.  <br><br>when casters see there life drop at all, they usually first think RUN!!!, but then the mob is suddenly off them, they don't need to run, then they remember why they are casters, they can kill a single mob really fast.  all the casters kick in, and finish it fast.  <br><br>of course this only works when they are not 0om.  do it the same way if they are.  just let the mob beat you for a bit if the root breaks.  never hit the mob in case a chanter uses mez on it.  chanters are a clerics best friend here.  that is why i always keep a symbol on my chanters.  a symbol will make you a friend in the group, chanters are the best friends to have when a tank is busy fighting already--tanks and chanters are usually the only members of the group to get the full line of buffs i can offer, pullers, too, if they are not the tank.<br><br>by the way, i read a post earlier from a high level cleric that usually only keeps superior heal ever mem'd.  greater heal fires quick, and does 300hp about.  a great spell to keep casters alive.  cheap mana, fast cast, can keep a chanter alive that is doing crowd control.  you don't want a chanter to go down in a big fight, trust me, it is bad for everyone.  the mobs usually agro you next.  you get hit, you can't heal.<br><br>i know the modern philosophy for clerics is to focus only on the tank.  this works perfectly when you are chain pulling.  you never have to heal anyone else.<br><br>what i am talking about is those bad situations that just happen because the game gets crazy some time.  and let me tell you, it feels a lot better coming out of those situations with everyone alive, not just you and a couple melee characters.<br><br>casters are part of the group, too.  they play an important role in taking down hard hitting mobs faster, and providing amazing crowd control, that saves the group in bad situations.<br><br>one or two greater heals thrown on casters can save 3 superior heals in the time saved on a mob beating your tank.  keep your casters alive as best you can.<br><br>with this said, there will be a time, when you have to choose between saving a caster and a tank.  pick the tank.  if the tank goes down, everyone dies, period.  i made the mistake of wasting tons of mana trying to keep another cleric alive.  he was nothing but a mana sink til he died.  i wasted too much mana to keep the tank up.  all he needed was one more heal to finish the last giant.  he didn't get it.  the group all died.  let my mistake be one you don't have to make.  you have to know when to let people die to save the rest of the group.<br><br>these are hard choices.  i just want to let the other clerics out there, that they have a responsibility to the other casters in their groups.  it isn't that hard to save them, it takes minimal mana, and saves tons of mana.  stun, and root.  throw a quick greater heal, take a short beating, and let the casters help you out, they will if they are worth grouping with.<br><br>which brings me to my next--long winded point--ATONE.  stun-root-atone.  ATONE clears the hate list.  one of the best tools in a clerics spell book for keeping mobs on the tanks.  explain to your group what atone is, a lot of people don't know clerics have a mem blur.  mostly because it is under used.  atone will save casters all day.  mostly bad casters that nuke too quick.  i personally like my casters to start nuking when the mob is 50% dead.<br><br>another way to keep casters alive is fear.  make sure the mob is snared first, this can be worked out with group members in advance.  fear kiting with snare is one of the most effective killing tools in the game.  i like to group wtih necros for this reason.  talk about being an experience leech.  i was in a group in the OT that fear kited for about 5 hours.  i basically buffed the 2 melee guys in the group the whole time.  i don't remember ever having to cast a heal spell.  mostly just to top people off.  i was even healing the necro cause i had mana surplus the whole time.<br><br>this was too long and i am sorry for that.  just thought i would share some ideas with my fellow clerics.  mostly trying to help new clerics that have noticed it difficult to keep casters alive.  i will say this as a warning, stun and root will be resisted a lot if you are under the level of the mobs.  atone isn't til 34.  and your casters will die.  <br><br>just take it in stride.  and remember, you will have to die for your group.  it is your job.  do not gate out of trouble, and never be the first to zone.  you can throw heals at people running to zone that will keep them alive.  save your divine aura to clear mobs or make a safe retreat after your group is clear.  remember, if you aren't willing to die for your group, you don't deserve the great honor it is to be among the cleric ranks.  and it is an honor.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
